{
  "text": "where α and δ are control parameters. Unlike sigmoid function, the squared loss function has greater gradient for large d, which gives more penalty for the severe false verification segments. To give an intuitive illustration, we borrow a figure from [CITATION_1] ) and show it in Fig. 3 . ",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "15396394"
